"Balanyà J., Solé E., Oller J.M., Sperlich D., Serra L.","Long-term changes in the chromosomal inversion polymorphism of Drosophila subobscura. II. European populations",2004,"Journal of Zoological Systematics and Evolutionary Research","42","3",,"191","201",,,10.1111/j.1439-0469.2004.00274.x,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-4043162010&partnerID=40&md5=d01b26e84c745d97452524ca9c802582","Departament de Genètica, Facultat de Biologia, Universitat de Barcelona, Barcelona, Spain; Departament d'Estadística, Facultat de Biologia, Universitat de Barcelona, Barcelona, Spain; Universität Tübingen, Biologisches Institut, Tübingen, Germany; Departament de Genètica, Facultat de Biologia, Universitat de Barcelona, Diagonal 645, 08028 Barcelona, Spain; Departament d'Estadística, Facultat de Biologia, Universitat de Barcelona, Diagonal 645, 08028 Barcelona, Spain; Universität Tübingen, Biologisches Institut, Morgenstelle 28, D72076, Tübingen, Germany","Balanyà, J., Departament de Genètica, Facultat de Biologia, Universitat de Barcelona, Barcelona, Spain, Departament de Genètica, Facultat de Biologia, Universitat de Barcelona, Diagonal 645, 08028 Barcelona, Spain; Solé, E., Departament de Genètica, Facultat de Biologia, Universitat de Barcelona, Barcelona, Spain, Departament de Genètica, Facultat de Biologia, Universitat de Barcelona, Diagonal 645, 08028 Barcelona, Spain; Oller, J.M., Departament d'Estadística, Facultat de Biologia, Universitat de Barcelona, Barcelona, Spain, Departament d'Estadística, Facultat de Biologia, Universitat de Barcelona, Diagonal 645, 08028 Barcelona, Spain; Sperlich, D., Universität Tübingen, Biologisches Institut, Tübingen, Germany, Universität Tübingen, Biologisches Institut, Morgenstelle 28, D72076, Tübingen, Germany; Serra, L., Departament de Genètica, Facultat de Biologia, Universitat de Barcelona, Barcelona, Spain, Departament de Genètica, Facultat de Biologia, Universitat de Barcelona, Diagonal 645, 08028 Barcelona, Spain","The chromosomal polymorphism of 13 European populations of Drosophila subobscura has been compared with that of the same populations collected 15-35 years ago. The chromosomal polymorphism of the old populations differs significantly from that of the new populations, mainly for chromosomes U and O. There is a very good agreement between the geographical space and the genetic space as shown by a graphical representation of the 26 statistical populations (13 old and 13 new) obtained by a principal coordinate analysis. This reflects both the existence of significant latitudinal clines for the frequencies of some chromosomal arrangements in the old and new samples and systematic changes that have taken place in these populations during the period that elapsed between the two surveys. An increase in the frequency of those arrangements typical of southern latitudes and a decrease for those common in northern latitudes is observed in all populations - Mediterranean, Atlantic and Central European. Furthermore, the genetic distances of the new populations to a southern population of reference have decreased in comparison with those of the old populations. These changes could be the result of climatic factors that are correlated with latitude. In particular, the assumption that global warming is responsible for all the changes observed appears rather likely. Whether these systematic changes of the chromosomal polymorphism are a consequence of local adaptations or have been produced by migration from the south remains an open question.","Chromosomal polymorphism; Drosophila subobscura; Global warming; Latitudinal clines","polymorphism; Drosophila subobscura",,,,,,"Anderson, W.W., Arnold, J., Baldwin, D.G., Beckenbach, A.T., Brown, C.J., Bryant, S.H., Coyne, J.A., Moore, J.A., Four decades of inversion polymorphism in Drosophila pseudoobscura (1991) Proc. Natl. Acad. Sci. USA, 88, pp. 10367-10371; Ayala, F.J., Serra, L., Prevosti, A., A grand experiment in evolution: The Drosophi